					<description><![CDATA[<p>Not everyone likes children, and that's okay. Being child-free is a valid and respectable lifestyle choice. However, it's important to understand how to navigate social situations with families in a respectful and courteous manner. Learn more about this topic here.</p>
<p>The post <a href="/2023/05/01/you-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster/">You don’t like children? Are you a monster?</a> first appeared on <a href="">The New Vibes</a>.</p>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_whatsapp" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/whatsapp?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="WhatsApp" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_linkedin" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/linkedin?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="LinkedIn" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_wordpress" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/wordpress?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="WordPress" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_copy_link" href="https://www.addtoany.com/add_to/copy_link?linkurl=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&amp;linkname=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" title="Copy Link" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save addtoany_share" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=%2F2023%2F05%2F01%2Fyou-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster%2F&#038;title=You%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20children%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20monster%3F" data-a2a-url="/2023/05/01/you-dont-like-children-are-you-a-monster/" data-a2a-title="You don’t like children? Are you a monster?"></a></p><p><span style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px;">Last Sunday I was tricked into attending my 2yr old cousin’s birthday party. I was under the impression that my older cousins were going to be there, and it was going to be a family get-together. When I got there, there were no older cousins, just a bunch of children, over 20 in number. 10 minutes into my arrival, I was breathless and so uncomfortable. I badly needed to leave but I managed to spend some 4 Herculean hours there.  Telling your family you don’t like kids is not something you can say to a typical Ghanaian family. </span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/mxRSQpLXBBqhjrOzcW" width="480" height="480" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">Being nurturing is something that some people believe comes naturally to women. But after spending the majority of my childhood, teenage years, and early part of my early 20s taking care of my little siblings, I beg to differ. After all these years, I still don’t like children around me. Sometimes I feel a little bit of resentment because I feel I could have enjoyed growing up better if I didn’t feel saddled with responsibilities. Being female felt so tiring. You’re expected to cook, clean, train, and nurture while pursuing academic or career excellence. It just felt too much to deal with.</p>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">Don’t get me wrong, I don’t hate children. Yes, I’d opt out of holding a baby but that’s just because I find them too delicate.  I’ve volunteered at some children-focused NGOs and my YouTube feed is filled with cute videos of babies walking around like miniature drunks. Children are bundles of joy and it’s a delight to watch them play. But that’s where the liking ends. I can’t deal with the noise, their sense of entitlement and I can’t deal with their disobedience and lack of organization. But then again, they are children and so I need to cut them a lot of slack. That’s why I prefer to like them from afar.</p>
<blockquote style="border: none; margin: 0px 0px 0px 40px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;"><p><iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/E9EN2Ql6NjXO" width="480" height="360" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p></blockquote>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">A while ago, I realized I wasn’t the only one who felt this way about children. I was speaking with a friend who opened up about not liking children too. She felt disturbed and wanted to do something about it. Guess what she did, she volunteered to teach Sunday school kids at church. Lol. Well, long story short, she’s still a Sunday school teacher but she still doesn’t like kids (she should stop right? hehe). Now here’s the thing, people aren’t even allowed to say things like this in our part of the world. You can’t say you don’t like kids lest you end up barren.  But here’s what I believe, not liking kids is not the same as not wanting kids. But, if you don’t want them at all too, no pressure but I want 2 boys someday.</p>
<blockquote style="border: none; margin: 0px 0px 0px 40px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;"><p><iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/1e4CgsRnTQJFK" width="480" height="480" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p></blockquote>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">Not being nurturing is nothing to be ashamed of, it’s not a defect and thus, doesn’t make you less of a woman. It’s something you can learn, in fact, it’s something everyone can learn regardless of gender. My family bashed me about not wanting to cook (I guess you already get the picture that I don’t do well with supposedly feminine roles) but when I moved out, I haven’t been eating out but hunger hasn’t killed me yet. Certain things come with time and being nurturing is one of them. (A special thanks to all the food channels that saved my life. S/O to Ndudu by Fafa especially Lol)</p>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">Some people are naturally not nurturing and have no maternal instincts. I read that it could be as a result of how they were cared for or not cared for as children. For some, that’s just their make-up. I fall in all 3 categories. There is also the feminist bit where women feel being required to nurture is sexist. But away from that, it’s ok not to be naturally nurturing because fun fact, this won’t necessarily make you a bad mother. If you give birth right now, certain things will come naturally to you, and the roles that don’t come immediately to you, you will grow into. Remember, it can be learned, fret not.</p>
<blockquote style="border: none; margin: 0px 0px 0px 40px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;"><p><iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/jF9gFVcrNoN7q" width="480" height="331" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p></blockquote>
<p style="background-color: white; color: #383838; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 0.875em;">So breathe, you aren’t a monster because you don’t like children.</p>
